      "text": [
        " : «لَوْ أَنَّ عَبْداً حَجَّ عَشْرَ حِجَجٍ كَانَتْ عَلَيْهِ حَجَّةُ اَلْإِسْلاَمِ إِذَا اِسْتَطَاعَ إِلَى ذَلِكَ سَبِيلاً »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2888 - Misma' ibn Abdul-Malik narrated from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"If a servant performs ten Hajj pilgrimages, the Hajj of Islam is still obligatory upon them when they become capable of fulfilling it.\""
        ]
      }
